Surprising widescreen and stereo, good quality

Hilarious classic crazy-comedy with insane musical elements, a soap opera from ancient Rome as told by a sleek slave played by Zero Mostel from the original 'The Producers / Springtime for Hitler, (1968)'. Won Oscar for Best Music, Scoring of Music, Adaptation or Treatment - and a Golden Globe for Best Motion Picture - Musical/Comedy.

After having laughed at old and worn vhs tapes for years, we were pleasantly surprised when the dvd finally was released as widescreen with stereo sound.

This is not my rip, but it's good quality, burn tested, runs well in my DivX player.
